<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0, viewport-fit=cover">
    <title>B.Ed | Bachelor of Education – Teaching Professional Degree</title>
    <!-- Google Fonts & Font Awesome -->
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:opsz,wght@14..32,300;14..32,400;14..32,500;14..32,600;14..32,700;14..32,800&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.0.0-beta3/css/all.min.css">
    <style>
        * {
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            box-sizing: border-box;
        }

        body {
            font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
            background: #f9fafb;
            color: #1e293b;
            line-height: 1.5;
            scroll-behavior: smooth;
        }

        :root {
            --primary-blue: #2563eb;
            --primary-dark: #1e40af;
            --accent-indigo: #4f46e5;
            --soft-bg: #eff6ff;
            --gray-light: #f3f4f6;
            --shadow-sm: 0 4px 12px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.04);
            --shadow-md: 0 12px 24px -8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
        }

        .container {
            max-width: 1280px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            padding: 0 24px;
        }

        /* navigation */
        .navbar {
            background: white;
            box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
            position: sticky;
            top: 0;
            z-index: 100;
            border-bottom: 2px solid var(--primary-blue);
        }
        .nav-flex {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: space-between;
            align-items: center;
            padding: 1rem 0;
            flex-wrap: wrap;
        }
        .logo h1 {
            font-size: 1.7rem;
            font-weight: 800;
            color: var(--primary-blue);
            letter-spacing: -0.3px;
        }
        .logo span {
            font-size: 0.8rem;
            font-weight: 500;
            color: #5b6e8c;
            display: block;
        }
        .nav-links a {
            margin-left: 28px;
            text-decoration: none;
            font-weight: 600;
            color: #2c3e50;
            transition: 0.2s;
            padding-bottom: 5px;
            border-bottom: 2px solid transparent;
        }
        .nav-links a:hover, .nav-links a.active {
            color: var(--primary-blue);
            border-bottom-color: var(--primary-blue);
        }

        /* hero */
        .hero {
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #eef2ff 0%, #e0e7ff 100%);
            padding: 3.5rem 0 4rem;
            border-radius: 0 0 48px 48px;
        }
        .hero-grid {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
            gap: 2.5rem;
            align-items: center;
        }
        .hero-text h2 {
            font-size: 2.7rem;
            font-weight: 800;
            line-height: 1.2;
            color: #1e293b;
        }
        .hero-text h2 span {
            color: var(--primary-blue);
            border-bottom: 4px solid #facc15;
            display: inline-block;
        }
        .hero-text p {
            font-size: 1.1rem;
            margin: 1.2rem 0 1.8rem;
            color: #334155;
        }
        .btn-hero {
            background: var(--primary-blue);
            border: none;
            padding: 12px 28px;
            font-weight: 600;
            color: white;
            border-radius: 40px;
            font-size: 1rem;
            cursor: pointer;
            display: inline-flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 10px;
            transition: 0.2s;
            box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
        }
        .btn-hero:hover {
            background: var(--primary-dark);
            transform: translateY(-2px);
        }
        .hero-image {
            background: #ffffffcc;
            border-radius: 32px;
            padding: 1.5rem;
            text-align: center;
            backdrop-filter: blur(2px);
            box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
        }
        .hero-image i {
            font-size: 7rem;
            color: var(--primary-blue);
        }
        .hero-image p {
            font-weight: 600;
            margin-top: 12px;
        }

        /* section style */
        .section {
            padding: 4rem 0;
        }
        .section-title {
            text-align: center;
            font-size: 2.2rem;
            font-weight: 800;
            margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
            position: relative;
            color: #1e293b;
        }
        .section-title:after {
            content: '';
            position: absolute;
            bottom: -12px;
            left: 50%;
            transform: translateX(-50%);
            width: 80px;
            height: 4px;
            background: var(--primary-blue);
            border-radius: 4px;
        }

        .card-grid {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
            gap: 2rem;
            margin-top: 1rem;
        }
        .card {
            background: white;
            border-radius: 28px;
            padding: 1.8rem;
            box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
            transition: all 0.25s ease;
            border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
        }
        .card:hover {
            transform: translateY(-5px);
            box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
            border-color: var(--primary-blue);
        }
        .card i {
            font-size: 2.6rem;
            color: var(--primary-blue);
            margin-bottom: 1rem;
        }
        .card h3 {
            font-size: 1.5rem;
            margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
            font-weight: 700;
        }

        .two-col {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
            gap: 2.5rem;
            align-items: start;
        }
        .info-card {
            background: white;
            border-radius: 28px;
            padding: 2rem;
            box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
            border-left: 6px solid var(--primary-blue);
        }
        .badge {
            background: var(--primary-blue);
            color: white;
            display: inline-block;
            padding: 0.3rem 1rem;
            border-radius: 60px;
            font-weight: 600;
            font-size: 0.75rem;
            margin-bottom: 1rem;
        }

        .stats-grid {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
            gap: 1.5rem;
            text-align: center;
            margin: 2rem 0;
        }
        .stat {
            background: white;
            padding: 1.5rem;
            border-radius: 28px;
            box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
        }
        .stat h4 {
            font-size: 2.2rem;
            font-weight: 800;
            color: var(--primary-blue);
        }

        footer {
            background: #0f172a;
            color: #cbd5e6;
            padding: 2.5rem 0;
            text-align: center;
            margin-top: 2rem;
        }

        @media (max-width: 768px) {
            .hero-grid, .two-col {
                grid-template-columns: 1fr;
                text-align: center;
            }
            .hero-text h2 {
                font-size: 2rem;
            }
            .nav-flex {
                flex-direction: column;
                gap: 0.8rem;
            }
            .nav-links a {
                margin: 0 12px;
            }
            .stats-grid {
                grid-template-columns: 1fr;
            }
            .section-title {
                font-size: 1.8rem;
            }
        }

        .highlight {
            color: var(--primary-blue);
            font-weight: 700;
        }
        .list-styled {
            list-style: none;
            padding-left: 0;
        }
        .list-styled li {
            margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 10px;
        }
        .list-styled li i {
            color: var(--primary-blue);
            width: 24px;
        }
        .syllabus-grid {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(240px, 1fr));
            gap: 1.2rem;
            margin-top: 1rem;
        }
        .syllabus-item {
            background: var(--gray-light);
            padding: 1rem;
            border-radius: 20px;
            font-weight: 500;
            text-align: center;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
<%- include('partials/Navbar') %>


<!-- Hero Section -->
<section class="hero">
    <div class="container hero-grid">
        <div class="hero-text">
            <div class="badge" style="background: #facc15; color:#1e293b;">Shape the Future</div>
            <h2>Bachelor of <span>Education (B.Ed)</span><br>Your Path to Professional Teaching</h2>
            <p>B.Ed is a professional undergraduate degree that prepares aspiring teachers for primary, secondary, and senior secondary levels. It focuses on pedagogical skills, educational psychology, and practical training to develop competent and compassionate educators.</p>
            <button class="btn-hero" onclick="alert('B.Ed: The gateway to a rewarding teaching career. Contact NCTE-approved colleges for admission.')"><i class="fas fa-graduation-cap"></i> Explore B.Ed Program</button>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-image">
            <i class="fas fa-person-chalkboard"></i>
            <i class="fas fa-book-open" style="font-size: 4rem; margin-left: 10px;"></i>
            <p>Inspiring Minds · Building Nations</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- Introduction -->
<div class="container section">
    <h2 class="section-title">What is B.Ed?</h2>
    <div class="two-col">
        <div class="info-card">
            <i class="fas fa-university" style="font-size: 2rem; color:var(--primary-blue);"></i>
            <h3 style="margin: 0.8rem 0 0.5rem;">Program Overview</h3>
            <p>Bachelor of Education (B.Ed) is a 2-year professional degree (4 semesters) offered by universities and colleges approved by the National Council for Teacher Education (NCTE). It is mandatory for teaching at the secondary and higher secondary levels in India. The course integrates theory and practice through classroom instruction, internship, and hands-on teaching experience.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="info-card">
            <i class="fas fa-users" style="font-size: 2rem; color:var(--primary-blue);"></i>
            <h3 style="margin: 0.8rem 0 0.5rem;">Why Choose B.Ed?</h3>
            <ul class="list-styled">
                <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> Eligible for teaching positions in government & private schools</li>
                <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> Pathway to competitive exams like CTET, UGC NET, and state TET</li>
                <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> Develops communication, leadership, and emotional intelligence</li>
                <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> Stable career with social respect and job security</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<!-- Eligibility -->
<section id="eligibility" class="container section" style="background: var(--soft-bg); border-radius: 48px; padding: 3rem 2rem;">
    <h2 class="section-title">🎓 Eligibility Criteria</h2>
    <div class="card-grid">
        <div class="card">
            <i class="fas fa-user-graduate"></i>
            <h3>For B.Ed (General)</h3>
            <p>Bachelor's degree (BA, B.Sc, B.Com) with minimum 50% marks (45% for reserved categories) from a recognized university.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
            <i class="fas fa-flask"></i>
            <h3>For B.Ed (Science)</h3>
            <p>B.Sc degree with relevant science subjects. Some universities require specific subject combinations for teaching science.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
            <i class="fas fa-language"></i>
            <h3>For B.Ed (Arts)</h3>
            <p>BA with subjects like History, Geography, Political Science, Economics, or Languages to teach at secondary level.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
            <i class="fas fa-calculator"></i>
            <h3>For B.Ed (Commerce)</h3>
            <p>B.Com degree to qualify for teaching Commerce and Business Studies in schools.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="stats-grid" style="margin-top: 1rem;">
        <div class="stat">
            <h4>50%</h4>
            <p>Minimum aggregate in Bachelor's (General)</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stat">
            <h4>2 Years</h4>
            <p>Program Duration</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stat">
            <h4>NCTE</h4>
            <p>Approved curriculum & recognition</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- Admission Process -->
<section id="admission" class="container section">
    <h2 class="section-title">📝 Admission Process & Entrance Exams</h2>
    <div class="two-col">
        <div class="info-card">
            <i class="fas fa-file-alt"></i>
            <h3>Common Admission Steps</h3>
            <ul class="list-styled">
                <li><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> Appear for state or university-level entrance exam</li>
                <li><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> Qualify written test (General Knowledge, Teaching Aptitude, Reasoning)</li>
                <li><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> Counseling and seat allotment based on merit</li>
                <li><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> Document verification and fee payment</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="info-card">
            <i class="fas fa-trophy"></i>
            <h3>Major B.Ed Entrance Exams</h3>
            <ul class="list-styled">
                <li><i class="fas fa-school"></i> <strong>DU B.Ed</strong> – Delhi University</li>
                <li><i class="fas fa-school"></i> <strong>BHU B.Ed</strong> – Banaras Hindu University</li>
                <li><i class="fas fa-school"></i> <strong>UP B.Ed JEE</strong> – Uttar Pradesh Joint Entrance Exam</li>
                <li><i class="fas fa-school"></i> <strong>MAH B.Ed CET</strong> – Maharashtra</li>
                <li><i class="fas fa-school"></i> <strong>Rajasthan B.Ed</strong> – PTET</li>
                <li><i class="fas fa-school"></i> <strong>CUET PG</strong> – For central universities (B.Ed)</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div style="background: #f1f5f9; border-radius: 28px; padding: 1.5rem; margin-top: 1.5rem; text-align: center;">
        <i class="fas fa-info-circle"></i> <strong>Note:</strong> Many universities also offer direct admission based on graduation marks. Check specific college requirements.
    </div>
</section>

<!-- Syllabus -->
<section id="syllabus" class="container section" style="background: var(--soft-bg); border-radius: 48px; padding: 3rem 2rem;">
    <h2 class="section-title">📚 B.Ed Syllabus (Core Subjects)</h2>
    <div class="syllabus-grid">
        <div class="syllabus-item">Philosophical Foundations of Education</div>
        <div class="syllabus-item">Sociological Perspectives in Education</div>
        <div class="syllabus-item">Psychology of Learning & Development</div>
        <div class="syllabus-item">Curriculum & Instructional Design</div>
        <div class="syllabus-item">Assessment & Evaluation</div>
        <div class="syllabus-item">Educational Technology & ICT</div>
        <div class="syllabus-item">Pedagogy of School Subjects (two methods)</div>
        <div class="syllabus-item">Internship & School Experience Program</div>
        <div class="syllabus-item">Creating an Inclusive School</div>
        <div class="syllabus-item">Guidance & Counselling</div>
        <div class="syllabus-item">Environmental Education</div>
        <div class="syllabus-item">Action Research in Education</div>
    </div>
    <p style="text-align: center; margin-top: 2rem;">In addition, students choose two teaching subjects (e.g., Mathematics, English, Social Science, etc.) and undergo a semester-long internship in affiliated schools.</p>
</section>

<!-- Career Opportunities -->
<section id="career" class="container section">
    <h2 class="section-title">💼 Career Opportunities After B.Ed</h2>
    <div class="card-grid">
        <div class="card">
            <i class="fas fa-chalkboard"></i>
            <h3>School Teacher</h3>
            <p>Primary, secondary, senior secondary teacher in government (KVS, NVS, state govt) and private schools after qualifying CTET/State TET.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
            <i class="fas fa-user-tie"></i>
            <h3>Educational Consultant</h3>
            <p>Work with schools, educational institutions, or EdTech companies to develop curriculum and teaching strategies.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
            <i class="fas fa-book"></i>
            <h3>Higher Studies & Research</h3>
            <p>M.Ed (Master of Education), Ph.D., or pursue NET/JRF for lectureship in colleges and universities.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
            <i class="fas fa-globe"></i>
            <h3>EdTech & Content Development</h3>
            <p>Create educational content, design learning materials, and work with online education platforms.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
            <i class="fas fa-counselor"></i>
            <h3>Counselor / Special Educator</h3>
            <p>With additional certification, work as school counselor, special educator, or inclusive education coordinator.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
            <i class="fas fa-hand-sparkles"></i>
            <h3>Civil Services / Administration</h3>
            <p>B.Ed graduates can appear for UPSC, state PSC, or become education officers in government departments.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="stats-grid">
        <div class="stat">
            <h4>₹3-8 LPA</h4>
            <p>Starting salary range (private schools)</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stat">
            <h4>Govt Pay Scale</h4>
            <p>Level 7–10 as per 7th CPC</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stat">
            <h4>100%</h4>
            <p>Placement assistance in reputed colleges</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- Top Colleges -->
<div class="container section" style="background: #f1f5f9; border-radius: 48px; padding: 2rem 2rem;">
    <h2 class="section-title">🏛️ Top B.Ed Colleges in India</h2>
    <div class="card-grid">
        <div class="card">
            <i class="fas fa-landmark"></i>
            <h3>Central Universities</h3>
            <p>DU (Delhi University), BHU, AMU, JMI, University of Hyderabad – renowned for B.Ed programs.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
            <i class="fas fa-building"></i>
            <h3>State Universities</h3>
            <p>Lucknow University, Mumbai University, Calcutta University, Madras University, etc.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
            <i class="fas fa-church"></i>
            <h3>NCTE-approved Private Colleges</h3>
            <p>St. Xavier's (Mumbai), Lady Irwin College (Delhi), Loyola College, etc.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
            <i class="fas fa-robot"></i>
            <h3>Distance / Open University</h3>
            <p>IGNOU, YCMOU, and state open universities offer B.Ed through distance mode (with mandatory practicum).</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<!-- Special notes about CTET/TET -->
<div class="container" style="margin: 2rem auto;">
    <div style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2563eb10, #4f46e510); border-radius: 32px; padding: 1.8rem; border-left: 5px solid var(--primary-blue);">
        <h3><i class="fas fa-certificate"></i> Mandatory Teacher Eligibility Tests (TET)</h3>
        <p>After B.Ed, candidates must clear <strong>CTET</strong> (Central Teacher Eligibility Test) for central schools (KVS, NVS) or <strong>State TET</strong> for state government schools. Many private schools also require TET qualification. Some states also conduct separate recruitment exams like DSSSB, REET, UPTET, etc.</p>
    </div>
</div>





<script>
    // smooth scroll for nav links
    document.querySelectorAll('.nav-links a').forEach(anchor => {
        anchor.addEventListener('click', function(e) {
            const href = this.getAttribute('href');
            if(href && href !== '#') {
                e.preventDefault();
                const target = document.querySelector(href);
                if(target) {
                    target.scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth', block: 'start' });
                }
            }
        });
    });
</script>
  <%- include('partials/footer') %>
</body>
</html>